After receiving the first dose of the COVID vaccine I was experiencing headaches, dizziness, lightheadedness, palpitations, and nausea. The first dose was on 12/21/20. These symptoms resolved around 12/26/20. I received the second dose of the COVID vaccine on 01/11/21. I began experiencing symptoms on 01/12/21. The symptoms I was experiencing were lightheadedness, dizziness, and brain fog/confusion. These symptoms got significantly worse from 01/13/21 - 01/24/21 and I began developing profound confusion/brain fog, diplopia, blurry vision, headaches, feeling like I'm swaying on a boat, and the "feeling of being drunk". As of 01/25/21, the symptoms have seemed to get better and I am starting to feel more like myself. The drunk feeling and mild blurry vision are still present as of today 01/28/21.

Close
10 minutes after the second dose, patient developed headache, lightheadedness, dizziness, shortness of breath/anaphylaxis. Transferred to ED, and experienced chest pain, SOB, tightness in throat. Patient was sent to the emergency department. Received 25 mg Benadryl prior to arrival as prophylaxis. Received Combivent in the ED, and symptoms improved. Patient was observed for 4 hours in the ED. Eventually patient was discharged home.

Close
I had a blood report taken on the 25th of February as a part of my physical. I have never had elevated platelets, but this report showed my platelets at at 499 (130-450 is reference ranges of the lab). A year ago, my platelets were just below the max at 445. Upon discussing with my PA, he didn't feel too concerned, but after asking if the first dose covid shot may have something to do with it, that became a potential etiology. I am very unsure of my elevated platelets is associated with the first dose. Arm was stiff on injection date for approximately 6 hours. Felt slightly flu like symptoms (headache, dizziness, fatigue) that same evening of injection date and felt fine the next morning. Blood specimen was taken on 25th of February 2021. Diet at the time is a ketogeneic diet. I'd like to make it clear I mean no deception and am unsure if there is an association with the vaccine and platelet levels, but my elevated platelets is inconsistent with any other blood report in the past, and the dose 1 covid vaccine was the only "new" thing in my life prior to the blood draw. I figured, better to let y'all know in case it became relevant. Currently on no treatments for the platelets and was told to "not worry about it" which is hard for me to just take.

26 2021-03-15 joint range of motion decreased, mobility decreased On 2/13/2021, I began to experience both enhanced and new musculoskeletal and neurological symptoms ... Read more
Close
On 2/13/2021, I began to experience both enhanced and new musculoskeletal and neurological symptoms that have not completely resolved still, today, 3/16/2021. While I had experienced some slight discomfort and pain of the b/l thumbs 2-3 weeks prior to 2/13, I began to experience increased pain up to the forearm in both arms on that day. In addition to pain, I had large muscular knots in the superior forearms, especially the right arm. The lower right arm felt extremely tight, and I was having difficulty raising the arm and gripping things. This continued for 2-3 weeks on the right arm. During that time, symptoms worsened on the left arm, while improving on the right arm. A week after the initial symptoms my left arm became worse, and I was struggling to lift objects as light as a sheet of paper. I was also having trouble typing at work, dialing the phone, and opening or closing my hand. Just over a week after symptoms began, I left work to determine a cause and solution for my issues. I also began to have tremors, extreme muscle spasms, and involuntary movements around this time for about 2-3 weeks. While the neurological symptoms have mostly subsided, still, today, 3/16/2021, I continue to deal with various inflammatory musculoskeletal symptoms affecting mostly my left arm, but also my right arm. Since yesterday, my left shoulder has begun to have pain as well, making raising my arm and reaching to the opposite side difficult due to pain. I have also had persistent popping of various joints in both arms since the initial symptoms began.

ED Note: At 1650, patient was observed following another nurse to the observation area, when he began swaying from side to side, lost consciousness and landed on his right side. The patient c/o left knee pain but denied any other symptoms. This nurse again checked his vital signs at 1655: 85/52, pulse ox 100%, pulse 86. At this point, rapid response was called and report was given. This nurse moved the patient to a wheelchair to prepare for transport to the E.R. The patient denied any further symptoms at this time except pain in his left knee. This nurse checked his vital signs at 1658: 102/64, pulse ox 100%, pulse 59. Rapid response arrived and this nurse gave report to them. Patient was transported to the E.R. via stretcher. No further issues noted at this time. Pt reports he has a history of getting nervous and "passing out" when getting blood drawn or getting a shot. Pt stated that when he stood up after getting his covid vaccine he felt lightheaded and passed out. ED staff responded to vaccine clinic At 1658 where pt's VS were as follows: 102/64 HR: 59 Sats 100% At present time, pt reports feeling "totally normal" and does not feel that he needs to stay to be seen in ED. I took him into the clinic room and allowed him to lay down and began to fan him down for him to cool off. After 1-2 minutes, we put him on his back and elevated his feet. After 5 more minutes, I told him to get up and slowly walk to another chair in the room. The patient's partner then informed me that he has a fear of needles and the last time he received a vaccination about 7 years ago, the same reaction happened.

Patient unresponsive; presented with seizure like activity; Patient fall from chair within 15minutes of receiving Pfizer vaccine dose 1; pale; diaphoretic; nausea; Full body clonus; This is a spontaneous report from a contactable nurse. A 26-year-old male patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, solution for injection) (at 26 years of age), dose 1 intramuscular, administered in arm left on 03Apr2021 10:45 (Batch/Lot Number: ER8737) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunisation. The patient's medical history included penicillin allergy. The patient's concomitant medications were not reported. The patient had no other vaccine prior to Covid vaccine. He was not diagnosed with COVID-19 prior to vaccination. It was unknown if patient has been tested for COVID-19 since the vaccination. It was reported that the patient fell from chair within 15 minutes of receiving Pfizer vaccine dose 1. Patient was unresponsive, pale, diaphoretic. Awakened within minutes, placed in recovery position on left side. Patient complained of nausea then presented with seizure like activity. Full body clonus. 911 notified. Patient woke within seconds able to state, name, location, date of birth accurately. He was placed on stretcher. EMS arrived. VS 154/80 HR 84, POx99% 2LO2. He continues to be pale. Family of patient notified of event at patient's request. He was transferred to ED via EMS. The events started on 03Apr2021 at 10:45 AM (as reported). Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of the events. The outcome of the events was unknown. Additional information has been requested.; Sender's Comments: Bases on the information in the case report and a strong temporal relationship, A causal relationship between adverse events Unresponsive to stimuli, Seizure and suspect product BNT162B2 cannot be excluded. The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to regulatory authorities, Ethics Committees, and Investigators, as appropriate.

26 2021-04-23 mobility decreased About two or three days after my second Pfizer vaccination I started to feel some immense pain in my... Read more
Close
About two or three days after my second Pfizer vaccination I started to feel some immense pain in my right trapezius. I had difficulty moving my neck for several hours. The pain subsided later that day but I still had adverse effects. I had a numbing and tingling feeling that traveled from my right trapezius all the way down to my fingers. That sensation continued for several weeks (3 or so) until I saw my general physician. She conducted some strength tests and noticed that there was some weakness and lack of coordination on my right side. I was instructed to go get and MRI and the results showed 5 lesions in my brain and 1 in my cervical spine (C2-C3). After many other tests including blood tests and a follow up MRI the neurologist that viewed my case informed me that I showed a strong case of demylination and it looked likely that Multiple Sclerosis. The shot might have caused an immune response which allowed the MS to appear.

A 27-year-old male patient received the second dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE, Lot number EL1283), via an unspecified route of administration on 08Jan2021 at 13:30 (at the age of 27-years-old) as a single dose in the left arm for COVID-19 vaccination. Medical history included asthma exacerbation, GERD, childhood anemia, a retinal tear in the right eye all from unspecified dates and unknown if ongoing. The patient also reported medical history three episodes (June 2019, August 2019 and October2019) of anaphylaxis due to "Exercise Induced Anaphylaxis." Historical vaccinations included the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 MRNA VACCINE, lot number EH9899) on 21Dec2020 at 13:30 after which he experienced pain at the vaccination site which lasted twenty-four hours. The patient's past product use included adrenaline (EPIPEN), an unspecified corticosteroid and an unspecified antihistamine for past allergic reactions. The vaccine was administered in a hospital. Prior to the vaccination, the patient had not been diagnosed with COVID-19. Concomitant medications included ciclosportin (RESTASIS), azelastine (AZELASTINE), mometasone furoate (FLONASE), cetirizine hydrochloride (ZYRTEC) and omeprazole (PROTONIX) all for unknown indications from unknown dates and unknown if ongoing. Within four weeks prior to the vaccination the patient had received unspecified "allergy shots" He received "two shots" (one in each deltoid) on 15Dec2021 and "two shots" (one in each deltoid) on 05Jan2021. The patient reported that fifteen to thirty seconds after the second dose of the COVID-19 vaccination he felt lightheaded and a little short of breath. This lasted about eight minutes and then subsided. Approximately thirty to forty minutes (about 30 minutes after he left the facility) later the symptoms returned. He felt short of breath and he thought he was going to pass out. The symptoms included fatigue, shortness of breath lightheaded and feeling like passing out on and off for the next two to three hours. He stated he has completely recovered. He continued to say that he was feeling fine for three days then he began having bilateral cervical lymph pain greater on the left than right, a lot of posterior lymph pain in the back of his head (for two weeks on and off). These symptoms also resolved on their own. He also experienced ("a couple of days later") a sensation where he thought he was going to lose control of his muscles and lose consciousness. He also developed a sense that the was going to lose control of his mind with heaviness at the back of his head, left side. He went to the Emergency Room (date not provided) and they provided Valium. He also reports an Emergency Room visit on 13Jan2021 during which he underwent a CT scan of the head which was normal and a neuro consult suggesting occipital neuralgia and he was put on muscle relaxers. He also stated that experienced shortness of breath and chest tightness after his allergy shots on 26Jan2021 and he specified that he had never before had these reactions to his allergy shots. After that he had yet another possible allergic reaction after eating pizza on 30Jan which included throat swelling as well. He further stated that on 04Feb he had anaphylaxis vs asthma exacerbation. On the following day he developed a heaviness to his left occipital head with that same feeling of wanting to lose control of his muscles. He never had that before. He started Prilosec about one and one half weeks prior to the reporting date. In follow up the Other HCP reporter/patient answered "Yes" to the following questions (DCA) about symptoms experienced: Bilateral wheeze/bronchospasm, upper airway swelling, increased use of accessory respiratory muscles, dry cough, difficulty breathing (without wheeze or stridor, sensation of throat closure, tachycardia, nausea. These were reported without dates and without context with regard to the events reported initially. These were also reported as not requiring treatment and having recovered on unspecified dates. Lab data included three SARS COV 2 nasal swab tests (14Jan2021, 03Feb2021 and 11Feb2021) all of which were negative. Unspecified treatment was reported for the events anaphylactic reaction and mental impairment. The clinical outcomes of the events Anaphylaxis, loss of consciousness, dizziness, dyspnea, fatigue and lymph node pain were reported as recovered on an unspecified date in 2021. The clinical outcome of mental impairment, heaviness of head, chest tightness and occipital neuralgia were reported as unknown.

Gentle motions of readjustment to sitting and typing on computer still cause pain past limit of range of motion. Shoulder/arm cannot be raised to any meaningful height without pain. Patient tends to bring arm close to body to avoid pain, effectively resulting in frozen shoulder. PLEASE NOTE: Vaccine site was observed to be much higher up on shoulder than dose #1. The patient did not receive any other vaccine within 4 weeks prior to the vaccine. The patient lost his vision and hearing, essentially unresponsive and light-headed on 16Apr2021 at 14:30. Normally, he could tell 1-3 minutes in advance that he would black out. This time, it was about 30 seconds. A week after the palpitations started it started happening more frequently and I was feeling light headed and I went to ER. I was diagnosed with SVT and put on metoprolol to control my heart rate. 1 week after I was on metoprolol, I took my second dose. I was feeling a little dizzy after my second dose but it improved after like 10 minutes. I started getting very fatigued and difficult to concentrate after my second dose. I spoke to my doctor and we thought it was because of metoprolol. My cardiologist took me off metoprolol but the fatigue didn't stop and I started having aches in shoulders, arms, neck and back. The aches and fatigue was more severe in the morning. After a week of being off metoprolol I started waking up with chest pain. One day the pain was severe and I had aches in shoulders, arms, neck and back and my heart rate was around 140 so I went to ER. The doctors put me on carvedilol and my heart rate has been controlled but my body aches and fatigue has been going on. The cardiologist and my PCP aren't sure if SVT or the medication is causing my body aches and fatigue. The only other thing I could think of was the vaccine so I wanted to send this report.

After about an hour following my second COVID-19 Injection I began feeling warm. My forehead felt warmer so I figure I may have had a slight fever at that point. I received a metallic (Note I say metallic but I know it wasn't actually metal but that's simply the best way I can describe the taste I experienced) following the injection about 5 minutes after. My arm remained sore following and still remains sore as of this report. I experienced a decline in mental acuity following about an hour after injection. I began to feel lightheaded and exhausted to the point I was experiencing severe disorientation and confusion. I was having trouble putting sentences together and experienced a ringing sensation in the ears. I felt like I wasn't even present anymore. I couldn't comprehend things around me and apparently had conversations I don't even remember having. Note that at that point I had gotten home but don't even remember getting home. I just know that this did not begin to wear off until around 8:45pm when it was like someone flipped a switch and I suddenly was coherent again. It was an odd sensation to experience. The arm remained sore and the metallic taste returned briefly after this experience. I experienced a similar feeling from the HPV injection years ago, but just like this it was a temporary thing that resulted in no long term issues. However, I cannot tell you fully what we did the rest of the day until around 845-9 pm. I also remember becoming partly agitated after the injection like my body just all of a sudden took notice of something and shot into action. I had received my allergy injections this same day about two hours earlier as well and none of these reactions ever occur with those for me. I continued to drink liquid as far as I know as there were a few empty bottles of water next to me. I have no recollection of getting them. It's odd. There's just this brief moment in time that is just missing from my memory with a few short bits and pieces that are there like a puzzle with some missing pieces. I feel I became so fatigued I could not function. My emotions I remember were off and hard to control during this period too. I felt like I was having some random mood swings. I feel ok now though aside from the upset stomach occasionally and the fatigue and arm pain (but even the arm pain has partly decreased now). It all ceased. I have a number of health issues outside of this but have not experienced this long of a period of almost intermittent amnesia and incoherency following an injection before. I believe it made me that much more tired or reacted with one of my many conditions or genetic variants that perhaps may have been part of this. I'm happy to provide anything I can to help with this. I am greatly appreciative of all the CDC has done to get us this vaccine and continues to do to ensure our safety both before and after injection. It is commendable. I did fill out my survey through the V-Safe portal as well and will continue to follow up there should I have any changes. I have not sought medical care following this event as the coherency and such have seemed to resolve in regards to the vaccine injection. Only thing left are known side effects at this point besides an occasional increase in numbness and tingling that I already experience in my legs and feet. My absolute best guess for the cause is my immune system which already has some issues regulating (doesn't always like to learn everything it should and we are currently searching for an undiagnosed autoimmune disorder currently going on as well in me) on top of allergy shots today. it was perhaps just a bit too much demand on it all at once. But it seems to be balancing out again now.

Close
Received the vaccine at 10:;15 am on 4/14/2021 and had fatigue, slight chills, and a sore arm. By 4/16/2021 I felt normal until approx. 10pm when my right ear blocked up and I lost hearing in my right ear. On 4/17/2021 I treated it as a congestion issue with neti pot and decongestions but the ear remained blocked. After sleeping for approx 1 hour on 4/17/2021 I woke up at approx. 11pm with severe vertigo and nausea and vomited consistently for approx 1 hour. I could not get off of the floor and the right side of my face was fixated to the floor. Paramedics were called and I was taken to the ER where I was treated with anti-nausea medications and valium to reduce vertigo. A non contrast CT, blood panel, and stroke assessment were all normal with no sign of ear infection. I was release from the hospital at 10am on 4/19/2021. On 4/21/2021 I saw an ENT who performed a hearing exam revealing my right ear is completely deaf with normal left ear function. The ENT prescribed prednisone 10mg (63 tablets over 10 days). As of today (4/25/2021) I no longer have vertigo and nausea, but I still have no hearing in my right ear and have significant vestibular challenges and cannot walk safely unassisted without getting dizzy.

Immediately after the patient received the vaccination he stated that his arm felt numb. This seemed to concern him greatly although I reassured him that this reaction had been reported to me on other occasions and it was transient. I checked his blood pressure and pulse, both of which were normal, and he waited for about 20 minutes before returning to work where he received the shot. He returned to the pharmacy approximately 15 minutes later and stated that he felt dizzy, nauseous, and had blurry vision. His forehead felt cold and clammy to the touch and he was sweating. I had him sit, and checked his pulse again (still normal). He stated that his chest felt "cold and tired" but he was not having difficulty breathing. After observing him for some minutes I gave him a 50mg dose of Benadryl in case the reaction was allergic in nature. I observed him for at least 15 more minutes were he seemed calm and was able to speak on his cellphone to family so they could come and pick him up. In my opinion he seemed improved by the time he left but I counseled him to seek medical attention if his adverse feeling worsened. The patient was able to walk out of the Walmart without assistance. I called him at home around 5:20 pm and he sounded very sleepy but he had not yet had to seek further medical attention.

29 2021-01-03 balance disorder left sided weakness; it has weakened his heart; stutter; severe stroke like symptoms; Ventricular ta... Read more
Close
left sided weakness; it has weakened his heart; stutter; severe stroke like symptoms; Ventricular tachycardia/help keep his heart rate at bay; Loss of balance; extreme numbness and tingling in left hand and foot; tingling in left hand and foot; oral motor impairment; mouth weakness and not coordinated/mouth is fatigued easily; Issues finding words and trouble speaking; Issues finding words and trouble speaking; Ejection fraction down to 25%; The initial case was missing the following minimum criteria: adverse event. Upon receipt of follow-up information on 28Dec2020, this case now contains all required information to be considered valid. This is a spontaneous report from a contactable other healthcare professional (HCP). A 29-years-old male patient received bnt162b2 (lot number: EJ1685), intramuscular (deltoid left) on 21Dec2020 at 05:30 at 0.3 mL single (first dose) for Covid. Medical history was reported as "none". Concomitant medications were not reported. The patient previously received Flu vaccine in Oct2020 for immunization. The patient is an Occupational Therapist, and he called to report an adverse event that he experienced with the first dose of the COVID Vaccine. He received the vaccine last Monday, 21Dec2020 at 5:30AM before his shift at work, then 20 minutes later, he was having severe stroke like symptoms. He experienced severe left sided weakness, loss of balance, extreme numbness and tingling in his left hand and foot, he had issues finding his words and he couldn't speak, and he had an oral motor impairment where his mouth was weak and not coordinated. The staff at the hospital did a neurological exam on him, and he failed, so he had to go to the emergency room (ER). The patient added that he was already in the hospital when this happened, and the ER doctors suspected that he had a CVA, and they gave him TPA to prevent any permanent brain damage and it worked. The patient then added that due to the shock of this whole event, from everything that happened, it has weakened his heart. Reportedly, he is a healthy 29 year old man, with no preexisting conditions, and he works out, and he has no heart conditions, but he had to get a cardiology follow up a few days after he got the vaccine, because he started going in to Ventricular Tachycardia, which he had never had in his life. So, the doctors at the hospital went ahead and did an Echocardiogram and an EKG, and he was told that his Ejection Fraction is down to 25%. He stated his heart is so weak, that he cannot work right now, but the structure of his heart is fine and has not had any damage. The hospital staff thought that maybe the patient had a chronic heart issue that he just did not know about, and that the stress of this event maybe made it kick into overdrive, but he states that the cardiologist said that was not the case, because the structure of his heart is fine, and the only thing they can see is that the heart is pumping weak. One physician even suggested that due to the shock of the event, he might have Takotsubo Cardiomyopathy, which is a broken heart, but because the structure of his heart is okay, it should be reversible. He stated that he is hoping he will heal up good, because he is young and has no pre-existing conditions. He added that his heart is in such a state right now; he has to wear an external defibrillator. The patient stated that all these happened about 20 minutes after he received the vaccine, and he was admitted to the hospital from 21Dec2020 to 25Dec2020. His neurological symptoms have resolved except that he has a stutter that he did not have before and his mouth is fatigued easily, so he has to slow down when he is eating, but now he can eat regular for the most part. The patient confirmed that he was not specifically prescribed the product; it was administered to him at his place of work, but it was optional. He stated he considered how he is working with COVID patients every day, and given the circumstance, he thought that it would be a best practice for him to get the vaccine. He had not gone to his primary care doctor in a while because he had been fine and healthy, but he called them and found out that his primary care had retired, so he has to find a new one now. Regarding the issues finding words and trouble speaking, he stated that he has improved, but it is still ongoing, he is just stuck in a plateau zone. With the Ventricular Tachycardia, he stated that this is an ongoing issue, as he has to wear the life vest even though he has no need to activate it yet. He did have one minor bought of the VTach, but because he is a therapist, he knows how to take care of it with relaxation techniques, he knows how to manage it. He had one bought of VTach the evening prior, but he was able to get it under control. The doctors have him on medication to help keep his heart rate at bay. He has never had to use medication before and is on the following medications to help keep his heart rate at bay: Metoprolol 25mg one tablet once daily by mouth and Lisinopril 5mg one tablet once daily by mouth. The VTach has improved, it was good enough he was able to discharge home, but it is still a concern. His cardiologist said that, basically his hope, is that once his body recover from the whole shock of everything, then his ejection fraction will heal, and his heart will heal. He again stated that the doctor told him that the structure of his heart is perfectly fine; he has thick walls in his heart, no leaking valves, and the heart was not conducting any abnormal signals. The doctor just said that right now, his heart is super weak and that it is an acute problem. With the Takotsubo Cardiomyopathy, he states that two doctors mentioned this diagnosis, but he confirmed that he was not actually diagnosed with this issue, he was just diagnosed with Ventricular Tachycardia. The outcome of the ejection fraction down to 25% was unknown to the patient at this time as he has not had another EKG or echocardiogram, but the cardiologist told him that the cardiologist expects that this will not be resolved quickly anyway. The patient confirmed that he did not receive any other vaccines on the same day he received the COVID vaccine. The only other vaccine he had this year was the flu vaccine which he got back in Oct2020. He has gone on to his online portal and there are the bloodwork results and all the imaging results on there from his CTs and MRIs, but he did not see the EKG or Echocardiogram results yet. He does not have this pulled up at this time, but he does have access to this stuff and can provide it later, if requested. He is curious about the next steps from here to how his case is processed. He is also curious if this information would help Pfizer make modifications to the vaccine if it is found that a lot of people are having the same reaction as he did. Then came the intense headache, body aches, and fatigue. This continued into the next day (Wednesday, December 23) prompting me to get COVID tested and take off of work on Thursday, December 24th. Nausea improved (5/10) on December 24th but fatigue, abdominal pain, and body aches did not. December 25-27 were slow improvements with nausea, abdominal pain, and fatigue but were limiting activities of daily living. By Monday, December 28th most symptoms had cleared.

There were no additional vaccines administered on same date of Pfizer suspect. Outcome of the events 'tightness to left trapezius and left side of neck, same side as vaccine'; 'increased pain and decreased range of motion to his neck' was recovering while unknown for the other events. My MRI was read the same day showing a demyelinating process. Multiple neurologist were consulted on this and they believe that my symptoms are not related to MS as the radiologist listed as his top three on his differential but rather what they called post-covid vaccine syndrome, similar to what they are seeing with patients who actually had COVID. I have no medical history, I am not taking any medications and had no symptoms prior to the vaccine. My symptoms were acutely brought on unlike MS and I do not have any of the four most common male characteristics of MS. I do not currently have any muscle weakness, I am not fatigued, it has not progressed to my upper extremities, it does not have a stalking glove approach but rather shoots down, I have no sexual dysfunction. I have been started on a high dose prednisone taper as recommended by the neurologist. My biggest concern is that when I looked for information as a medical provider, I was unable to find anything related to neurological issues and the vaccine. Once, I was placed in contact with multiple neurologist, I was told that they are seen quite a few neurological adverse events.

She notified personnel while we were in the 15 min wait holding area and when I regained consciousness two EMTs were checking me out. It was recommended I visit a hospital or urgent care if I continued to feel unwell. My wife & I left the vaccine site and decided on the way home to go to the hospital just to ensure everything was all right. We went back home for about 30-60 minutes. During this time my heart rate continued to remain elevated and it felt like I had adrenaline coursing through my system. I attributed the feeling to recovering from passing out, but it did not dissipate. Upon arrival to the ER I began having trouble trying to breathe and chest pain. During the triage EKG it was discovered I was experiencing atrial fibrillation. I was given treatment, fluids and monitored for several hours before being released. Estimated time from receiving shot to being diagnosed with afib was approximately 2.5-3 hours.

Close
My first COVID19 Pfizer vaccine shot was on 4/05/21. My second was 3 weeks later on 4/26/21. About 30 hours after my second vaccine on 4/27/21 I started to notice tightness around my lungs/rib cage in the intercostal muscle area. For the next few days the pain increased and I had shortness of breath as well. After a few nights I couldn't lie down to sleep because of this pain so I had to sit upright to sleep. On 5/3/21 I went to the doctor at hospital where I was examined and had a lung X-ray as well as a COVID PCR test (it was negative). The PA diagnosed me with "Pneumonia" and I was given antibiotics (cefuroxime and azithromycin) to take for 6-7 days. I started feeling a little better by 5/6/21 and actually reported here on VAERS with my diagnosis of suspected Pneumonia. On 5/17/21 I had another lung x-ray at hospital and was told my lungs were looking more clear. However, for the next 2 weeks I felt more tired and my poor breathing, a cough with bloody mucus, and more chest/rib cage area pain developed. Despite being a professional runner it became hard to walk up a flight of stairs without breathing really hard and feeling light-headed. On 5/30/21 I woke up with fairly intense chest pain just under my heart. I was taken to the ER at second Hospital and got a CT scan with contrast that showed a bilateral Pulmonary Embolism with infract. An ultra sound of my heart (normal) and blood panels were performed as well as multiple EKGs. I was given a stomach injection of Lovenox also. That afternoon I was transferred to third Hospital. for overnight monitoring with more EKGs and Lovenox injections. Prescribed blood thinner Pradaxa for 3 months with no known cause of clots that caused this Pulmonary Embolism. Kidney test and Heart appeared normal. Still waiting on genetic testing. Lung infract has caused lasting chest pain and my breathing has yet to return back to normal.

36 2021-03-03 dizziness Was administered the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine in our drive-thru clinic on 3/4/21 at approximately 2:1... Read more
Close
Was administered the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine in our drive-thru clinic on 3/4/21 at approximately 2:15pm. Was in the driver's seat of his SUV with his father in the passenger seat. Nothing in the PQCF gave us any reason to be concerned over this particular administration. After administration, was asked to pull forward and park in a spot on the right in order to sit for his required 15 minutes post-administration. became unresponsive as he was attempting to park and continue to turn the wheel causing him to drive in a U shape into a rock covered median. The SUV was able to clear the median and the car stopped at the APEX. When I saw the car heading towards the median, I started to head toward the site safely. I approached the car slowly asking him to stop. When I did not receive a response, I knew something was wrong. Once I felt the car was safe to approach, I ran to assist the patient. The patient was barely able to communicate but did say he was dizzy. 15 seconds later he was unable to communicate, I called a second pharmacist to run over with an epi pen just in case (this was NOT administered). I immediately called 911 at 2:21 pm. reached into the vehicle and got the vehicle into park, while I assessed his airway, breathing, and pulse from a seated position. The patient began to seize. I continued to hold the patient from outside of the vehicle to maintain the patient's airway and keep him from hurting himself on the steering wheel. The patient regained consciousness approximately 3 minutes later with no memory of what happened. EMS arrived on scene about 2 minutes after he regained the ability to communicate. While EMS assessed the patient, and I reached out to and division one store management per SOP. EMS determined that the patient had a seizure and was able to go home if they wanted. The father moved into the driver seat. We monitored the patient for 30 minutes and allowed them to leave. We followed up with the patient via phone 2 hours later with no concerns noted. No property damage or bodily harm occurred during this incident. If we are given approval to vaccinate this patient with a second dose, we will arrange for this patient to be taken care of in the pharmacy.

I got out of bed to get some water. When I exited the room the nausea intensified so I knelt on the floor to wait until it passed. It didn't really pass so I stood up to try and get back to the bed. When I came to, I was lying face down and still experiencing intense nausea. I was also very hot and sweating, and very thirsty. I laid with my eyes closed an breathing very heavily to suppress the urge to vomit for a minute or two. When the urge to vomit began to subside I took a few sips of water while still lying on the ground. After another minute or two I was able to get up and get back into bed. The extreme nausea subsided after a few more minutes and I was able to drink more water. I went back to sleep after that. I woke up in the morning around 7am. I felt a little "off" for most of the day: slightly weak, a mild headache, with some difficulty focusing. But since then I have felt normal. I didn't seek medical attention or take any medication. I have experienced Vasovagel Syncope as a child so I expect that I am more susceptible to fainting like in this case.

Close
After taking my 2nd Shot for Booster on the morning of Friday the 5th of 2021. I ate and hydrated for the day. At home I was resting when standing up I was overwhelmed with dizziness, nausea, sweats, and then the chills and heat hit. My inner core felt frozen. I couldn't move after standing up and the chills locked every bone in my body I couldn't breathe. Terrified doesn't cover how afraid I was at that moment. Teeth chattering, fingers rigid, and my back was solid. After moments in this state, I put on layers of sweaters to warm myself. The outside temperature was 65-70*C. So not that bad. I was in shock and not long after putting on my sweaters. My skin felt like it was sun burned and all the weight of the clothing was painful. I could not lay down, or even roll on my side for rest. Even standing up made my spin hurt. The muscles in my lower back seized up and the pain was right in the middle of my spin. (The ER Doctors checked and I do not have kidney stones.) I was fighting 99.3+ temp and rising. (This temp is accurate. I have phot evidence.) There was no sleep that Friday night. Saturday morning I called the first available chiropractor and went to that appointment at 2pm. As a new client they don't want to go all out in the first session, but I was in pain with every breathe. Hyperventilating and over breathing was causing issues with my head and stomach. The session was amazing, electro therapy mixed with heavy cracks worked on by a professional did help, but only for a brief period of time. Walking away from the building I was still in more pain than ever. My dad arrived to take me to the ER at roughly 6pm. Doctors gave me fluid and anti inflammatory drip. Potassium and Tylenol. It worked. The pain was unreal and I welcomed anything to end the suffering.

38 2021-06-02 mobility decreased On day 2 or 3 of getting the shot, I started feeling a burning sensation in my chest and what felt l... Read more
Close
On day 2 or 3 of getting the shot, I started feeling a burning sensation in my chest and what felt like my heart. It was about 3 or 4 out of 10 on the pain scale. I also had intermittent tingling sensations, mostly on my cheek to the left of my nose, but also tingling in locations around my body which happened only a couple of times. My heart beat rapidly. It was similar to the heart palpitations I get when I eat certain foods. It also felt as if my heart was constrained, as if its outer layers were less flexible than usual. When the symptoms showed up I started following a fairly aggressive anti-inflammatory diet, mainly wheat/cereal and Advil. I spent most of the time lying in bed facing up, in order to minimize strain on my heart. I had trouble laying on my side, since my chest/heart was sensitive to pressure. I also believe I was more acutely aware of the distribution of blood throughout my body, and laying on my side felt similar to being upside down in that blood was pooling heavily at the bottom, but I may be misremembering the sensation. I don't know if I had shortness of breath, since I took care to avoid exertion. Since my heart was beating like crazy, exertion of any kind seemed like a really bad idea. The symptoms did not change in severity for a couple days. On day 4 or 5 of getting the shot, I felt slightly feverish for about a 10 minute period. During this time, I noticed the burning sensation weakening slightly, and I began feeling a soreness on my chest near my left shoulder, which I believe is a lymph node area. Each day after, the symptoms and my heart calmed down little by little. ---- On day 9, I went to the emergency room since I still had heart palpitations and the burning sensation at about a 1/10 pain level. Just sitting upright caused my heart to go into overdrive. The hospital did not find anything out of the ordinary. I was given MAALOX, but the burning sensation was too faint to know if there was any improvement as a result. Their best theory is that I had costochondritis. ---- On day 11, after eating dinner I started getting "chronic hiccups". These last anywhere from 10 minutes to a couple of hours without stopping. I am not sure whether food or drinks cause them. They are short/acute hiccups and happen at an interval of about 10-15 seconds. I have no history of such a thing. ---- Today is day 12. The symptoms are noticeably better since I visited the hospital, but the burning sensation is still present around what feels like my heart and the hiccups aren't stopping. My best theory is that I may have had an infection by the time I got the vaccine. Maybe I had an infection, not necessarily COVID but some related virus, that was kept in check below an immune response threshold until the vaccine came along and led to the immune system burning the whole infection down.

12 Hours after my Husband's second Pfizer shot, he laid down and became incredibly lethargic, confused, delirious, achy, nauseous, and feverish, with shaking and chills. He collapsed when walking to the bathroom in the middle of the night, saying he couldn't breath. He was okay once he laid back down. He stayed in bed for 36 hours. 5 days later he is still fatigued, achy, and has headaches and eye strain, with intense pain in his arm, and a rash covering his body.

15 min. Observation ended at 4:08pm; patient complained of minute skin elevation on his left lower arm radiating to his upper arm. Patient voiced no itchiness on his arm. Benadryl P.O. given at 4:15pm. At 4:45pm, patient verbalized of slight dizziness. ER notified for further evaluation. Patient's vitals as follows: 182/101 ; HR-105/min; SPO2-96-98%. To ER per stretcher. Patient is alert and oriented, accompanied by ER nurse. ED Note: Patient is a 39 y.o. male with no significant medical history presents with an allergic reaction after his second Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine dose earlier today. Patient and his mother reports that patient received second dose of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine shot today at about 15:50. Before the 15 minutes observatory period was complete, patient and his mother noted that his arms became red, he was diaphoretic, and he developed "'chills and goosebumps." He denies itchiness or shortness of breath. He was given Benadryl at 16:10 today and requested a bed to observe him. His reaction prompted transfer to the ED. Patient reports he feels improved at this time. He denies taking any new medications and notes he had no issues after the first vaccination dose. Reevaluated patient. Patient feels improvement and is ready for discharge. The patient is comfortable with further observation of his symptoms at home. I discussed our workup, answered all questions and made sure there were no other concerns. I provided counseling about standard home and self-care measures and advised on standard return precautions including new, persistent, or worsening / concerning symptoms. Discharge Meds: famotidine 20 mg BID, fexofenadine 180 mg daily, prednisone taper x 6 days.

he may pass out; feeling cold; chills; high heart rate; headache; palpitations; dizziness; Sweating; like a panic attack; got more anxious and scared; This is a spontaneous report from a Pfizer Sponsored Program. A 39-years-old male patient received the first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), via an unspecified route of administration on 25Apr2021 12:30 (Batch/Lot number was not reported) as 1ST DOSE, SINGLE for covid-19 immunisation (Age at vaccination: 39 years). The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. The patient states he took the shot at 12:30PM and came out of the technician's room, sat on the chair, and at that time, a minute after, the first thing he developed was dizziness, he started with dizziness, followed by palpitations and sweating and chilling, then headache and then he started a little bit of panic, like a panic attack, a lot of people gathered around him, he was scared because of it, and then the technician came out and mentioned he needed to go to the ER as soon as possible or he may pass out, he is unsure what she meant, but it scared him more (all on 25Apr2021). At the time he took the vaccine, 3 days before the vaccine came, his father, who is not in the US, but back home, his father was tested positive for corona, was in ICU at the time of caller's vaccine, so caller was stressed for 3-4 days before the vaccine, but at that time didn't feel like complete anxiety like when he took the vaccine, he was fine, not scared, but was 100% fine, not scared, then took the shot, started symptoms, got more anxious and scared and when people gathered, sometimes he felt totally stressed out because of his father. At the same time, if you are anxious and scared your heart beat can be high but not that high, his heart beat was 164 the other day, not the same, day, but after 24 hours. 25th was when he had the shot, 26Apr2021, at 1PM he was talking to someone on the phone, felt chills and right away his heart beat went from 120-140, he took water and sat down, walked a couple steps and picked up his oximeter and checked his oxygen and his heart rate was 120 to 130 to 140 then 160, and he sat down, took water and relaxed, it dropped down to 120, was 120-130 some time for 15-20 minutes then 911 guys came, took him to the hospital, and by the time he was at the hospital he was in the 100s. Feeling cold and chilling outcome: He was feeling cold chills, is now pretty much normal, sometimes he feels chills because he is in a T-shirt, he was fine going into the room taking the vaccine, when he came out, the first symptoms he started feeling was dizziness and feeling like falling down. High heart rate: was only those instances for 2 days, on the 25th and 26th for a little time, 15-20 minutes each day, after that he went to the cardiologist, who put a heart rate meter on his chest and observed his rate for 24 hours, and beat, and took a heart ultrasound and bloodwork and all his blood is fine and his heart rate is fine, after that he visited 3 times the cardiologist, who said his beat was fine and function was fine, and he was healthy and his physician after checking the report, she said the blood reports pretty much were normal. All the events occurred on 25Apr2021 and patient had an emergency room visit for all of the events and had a physician office visit for the event high heart rate. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included blood work: normal, heart rate: normal, heart rate: 100-160 and heart ultrasound scan: normal on an unspecified date. Outcome of the event Depressed level of consciousness was recovered on an unspecified date while outcome of the event heart rate increased was recovered on 26Apr2021. Outcome of the events panic attack and anxious mood was recovered on an unspecified date in 2021. Outcome of the remaining events was recovered on Apr2021. Information on the lot/batch number has been requested.

On Saturday. May 29, I experienced pain similar to appendicitis. I drove to the nearest ER where after 29 minutes, I could barely walk from pain. After 2-3 hours of testing, it was found that my right kidney had a renal infarct and that I had lost up to 25% of my kidney to necrosis. I am not sure if this is an adverse reaction to the vaccine, but I wanted to enter it into the system just to be safe.
